  {
    "id": 1304950,
    "position": 4,
    "description": "<link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_74070000000000001/attachments/8409020/dp_app.css\"><ol>\n<li>Did Big Sur Ventures do anything wrong?&nbsp; How could they have avoided the situation expressed in Exhibit 1?</li>\n<li>What does risk mean in the context of a venture capital firm?&nbsp; For example, is risk in any way tied to the public markets?</li>\n<li>What dimensions constitute meaningful diversification to a venture capital firm, especially an early-stage venture firm?&nbsp; Geography? Sector? Stage?</li>\n<li>Which partner is managing which part of the portfolio?</li>\n<li>What mechanisms (organizational, administrative, or process based) would you suggest Big Sur Ventures implement to manage portfolio risk?&nbsp; What would be the cost?</li>\n<li>In the current Big Sur, how is the relationship of the partners key to portfolio management?</li>\n</ol><script src=\"https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_74070000000000001/attachments/8409019/dp_app.js\"></script>",
